channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Pope cancels his audiences due to slight illness days before a new trip
item.description: Pope Francis has canceled his audiences because of a “slight flu-like state” just days before he is to embark on a trip to Belgium and Luxembourg

item.title: What to know about Upbring, the Austin nonprofit that will run Head Start in Nueces County
Jane Fonda on climate activism, 2024 election: "We can't lose another 4 years"
item.description: Jane Fonda spoke with CBS News about why she joined the fight: "This isn't just about the environment. This is about the whole planet."

item.title: Israel hits 300 targets in expanded Lebanon strike campaign against Hezbollah
item.description: The Israeli military warned it would expand strikes across Lebanon early on Monday, as the long-simmering conflict with Hezbollah threatened to explode into larger war.

item.title: Dow Jones Futures: Stock Market Bulls Take Control; Meta, Apple, Tesla In Buy Areas
Jane Fonda on her climate activism and message for young voters: "Show us your power!"
item.description: Actor and activist Jane Fonda sat down with CBS News national environmental correspondent David Schechter to talk about her commitment to fighting climate change, why young voters are so important in 2024, and how she views her role as a celebrity activist. See more of her interview on "CBS Saturday Morning" on Sept. 28.

item.title: Ukraine's Zelenskyy visits Pennsylvania ammunition plant to thank workers and ask for more
item.description: It produces one of the most critically needed munitions for his country’s fight.

item.title: Fact Check: No, Pics Showing Young Kamala Harris 'Working as Escort' Aren't Real
Israel launches new strikes on Hezbollah in Lebanon, warns people to flee
item.description: Israel has launched a new wave of airstrikes targeting Hezbollah in Lebanon, with residents in some areas being warned to evacuate.

item.title: WATCH: Bulls escape from rodeo in Massachusetts
item.description: Eight bulls got loose from a rodeo at a Massachusetts mall. City officials urged residents to avoid the area and cowboys were spotted running and chasing after the animals.

item.title: This Immortal Creature Can Create a Form of Cancer That's Contagious
Florida's new COVID booster guidance is straight-up misinformation
item.description: State Surgeon General Joseph Ladapo spread anti-vaccine misinformation by telling Floridians to avoid mRNA vaccines. Vaccine experts and historians can't remember another state health leader urging residents to avoid an FDA-approved vaccine.

item.title: 21 people shot by multiple gunmen on Birmingham street, police say
item.description: Four people were killed and at least 17 injured in a shooting in Birmingham, Alabama, on Saturday night, police said.

item.title: See the iPhone 16’s game-changing battery removal process in new iFixit teardown
Dick Moss, lawyer behind free agency for baseball players, dies at 93
item.description: The Major League Baseball Players Association says Dick Moss, who revolutionized pay for professional athletes, has died at the age of 93 in California.
